FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - CHINA (04): (GANSU) SEROTYPE O, LIVESTOCK, OIE
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 13 Apr 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(16) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26418


Foot-and-mouth disease, China (People's Rep of)
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 13 Apr 2018 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Mar 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 11 Apr 2018
Report date: 13 Apr 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Apr 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: July 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of the outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Linxia Hui Autonomous Prefecture, Linxia, Gansu
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Mar 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: livestock market
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 35 / 2 / 0 / 35 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 5.71 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Legal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: Infected cattle were transported from Linxia county to Hami city, in the neighbouring province of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, traceability, quarantine, official destruction of animal products, stamping out, disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Lanzhou National Reference Laboratory Foot and Mouth Disease (OIE reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / gene sequencing / 11 Apr 2018 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 11 Apr 2018 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

